{
  "info": {
    "name": "MOKENGELI API",
    "description": "Collection API backend — préfixe /api/v1 (sauf Health racine).\nVariable `baseUrl` : https://localhost:3000 (chemin public HTTPS, sans mTLS).\nPour le listener mTLS (MTLS_ENABLED=true + port 8443), ajouter cert client dans Postman.\n\nTests Postman (onglet Tests) : point 6 du plan — exécuter la collection avec Runner.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "https://localhost:3000"
    },
    {
      "key": "beneficiaireId",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "sessionId",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "transactionId",
      "value": ""
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health (racine)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "pm.test(\"JSON success\", function () { var j = pm.response.json(); pm.expect(j.success).to.be.true; });",
              "pm.test(\"data.status ok\", function () { var j = pm.response.json(); pm.expect(j.data.status).to.eql(\"ok\"); });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
        "description": "GET /health — chemin public HTTPS (sans mTLS). Réponse { success, data } avec status ok."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Health API v1",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "pm.test(\"JSON success\", function () { var j = pm.response.json(); pm.expect(j.success).to.be.true; });",
              "pm.test(\"data.status ok\", function () { var j = pm.response.json(); pm.expect(j.data.status).to.eql(\"ok\"); });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/health",
        "description": "GET /api/v1/health — même payload que /health (étape 4.1)"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4.1 — Supabase ping (API v1)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "pm.test(\"success true\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true; });",
              "pm.test(\"supabase dans data\", function () { var d = pm.response.json().data; pm.expect(d).to.have.property(\"supabase\"); });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/health/supabase",
        "description": "Étape 4.1 — même logique que /health/supabase mais sous préfixe /api/v1"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4.2 — Contexte client + comptes (GET /me)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "pm.test(\"success true\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true; });",
              "pm.test(\"client + comptes\", function () { var d = pm.response.json().data; pm.expect(d).to.have.property(\"client\"); pm.expect(d).to.have.property(\"comptes\"); pm.expect(d).to.have.property(\"solde_total\"); });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/me?reference_client=C-501",
        "description": "Étape 4.2 — client, comptes avec solde_disponible, solde_total. Prérequis : migrations 001+005 et client existant (adapter reference_client)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4.3 — POST bénéficiaire (compte bancaire)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 201\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
              "pm.test(\"success true\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true; });",
              "var j = pm.response.json(); if (j.data && j.data.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set(\"beneficiaireId\", j.data.id); }"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"mode\": \"compte_bancaire\",\n  \"compte_identifiant\": \"CD-DEMO-0001\",\n  \"banque_code\": \"RAWBANK\",\n  \"titulaire_compte\": \"Marie Mbuji\"\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/beneficiaires",
        "description": "Étape 4.3 — migration 004. Optionnel : ajouter reference_client_lie si le bénéficiaire est un client connu."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4.3 — POST bénéficiaire (mobile money)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 201\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
              "pm.test(\"success true\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true; });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"mode\": \"mobile_money\",\n  \"telephone\": \"+243900000000\",\n  \"operateur_mobile\": \"Orange\"\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/beneficiaires",
        "description": "Étape 4.3 — mobile money"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4.3 — GET liste bénéficiaires",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "pm.test(\"liste\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().data.beneficiaires).to.be.an(\"array\"); });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/beneficiaires?limit=20",
        "description": "Étape 4.3 — liste (limit 1–100, défaut 50)"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4.3 — GET bénéficiaire par id",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "pm.test(\"id\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().data.id).to.exist; });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/beneficiaires/{{beneficiaireId}}",
        "description": "Étape 4.3 — lancer après POST banque qui remplit beneficiaireId, ou coller un UUID manuellement."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Supabase — ping (racine)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "pm.test(\"payload success\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true; });",
              "pm.test(\"supabase object\", function () { var d = pm.response.json().data; pm.expect(d).to.have.property(\"supabase\"); });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/health/supabase",
        "description": "Étape 4.1 — vérifie Auth /health Supabase (alias racine, pas de préfixe api)"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Transactions — Evaluate",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "pm.test(\"success true\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true; });",
              "pm.test(\"persistence\", function () { var d = pm.response.json().data; pm.expect(d).to.have.property(\"persistence\"); pm.expect(d.persistence.status).to.be.oneOf([\"persisted\",\"skipped\"]); });"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"transaction_event\": {\n    \"metadata\": {\n      \"numero_transaction\": \"TXN-DEMO-001\",\n      \"id_client\": \"C-501\",\n      \"montant\": 45000,\n      \"devise\": \"CDF\",\n      \"type_transaction\": \"P2P\",\n      \"canal\": \"mobile\"\n    }\n  }\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/transactions/evaluate",
        "description": "POST /evaluate — Zod ; étape 4.5 : persistance si métadonnées complètes + Supabase (sinon skipped)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4.5 — POST evaluate (persistance)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 200\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
              "pm.test(\"success true\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true; });",
              "pm.test(\"persistence\", function () { var d = pm.response.json().data; pm.expect(d).to.have.property(\"persistence\"); pm.expect(d.persistence.status).to.be.oneOf([\"persisted\",\"skipped\"]); });",
              "pm.test(\"persisted details\", function () { var p = pm.response.json().data.persistence; if (p.status === \"persisted\") { pm.expect(p.transaction_id).to.exist; pm.expect(p.numero_transaction).to.exist; } });",
              "var j = pm.response.json(); if (j.data && j.data.persistence && j.data.persistence.status === \"persisted\" && j.data.persistence.transaction_id) { pm.collectionVariables.set(\"transactionId\", j.data.persistence.transaction_id); }"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"session_id\": \"{{sessionId}}\",\n  \"transaction_event\": {\n    \"metadata\": {\n      \"numero_transaction\": \"TXN-4-5-{{$timestamp}}\",\n      \"id_client\": \"C-501\",\n      \"montant\": 1000,\n      \"devise\": \"CDF\",\n      \"date_transaction\": \"2025-03-24T10:00:00.000Z\",\n      \"type_transaction\": \"P2P\",\n      \"canal\": \"mobile\"\n    }\n  }\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/transactions/evaluate",
        "description": "Étape 4.5 — lancer après 4.4 (sessionId) pour lier la session ; numero_transaction unique via {{$timestamp}}. Sans session, retirer session_id du corps. Remplit transactionId si persisted."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4.4 — POST session (nouvelle, reference_client)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test(\"Status 201\", function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
              "pm.test(\"success true\", function () { pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true; });",
              "var j = pm.response.json(); if (j.data && j.data.session && j.data.session.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set(\"sessionId\", j.data.session.id); }"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"reference_client\": \"C-501\",\n  \"canal\": \"mobile\",\n  \"adresse_ip\": \"192.168.1.1\"\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/sessions",
        "description": "Étape 4.4 — crée une ligne sessions. Adapter reference_client. Remplit sessionId."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4.4 — POST session (mise à jour)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
